determining a value of blood pressure during rest condition of the patient, Pa, rest, at a position proximal in the coronary artery or proximally of any stenosis if present; and
determining a value of blood pressure during maximum hyperemia of the patient, Pa, hyper, at a position proximal in the coronary artery or proximally of any stenosis if present,
wherein the microvascular resistance reserve, MRR, is determined by the additional step of calculating the microvascular resistance reserve as

